    "As expected, classification performances on the diverse dataset slightly decrease, but overall remain very high.",
    "For the VH model, the biggest drop is found with rhesus sequences from a PR-AUC of 0.965 with the test set down to 0.923 with the diverse greater than 5% set (Fig. 2b, c).",
    "However, the VH model is still able to classify most of the diverse greater than 5% sequences as human.",
    "Only 5.5% of these sequences have a score below the nativeness threshold of 0.8, compared with 1.9% for the test VH sequences.",
    "For the light-chain models, the performances are even more comparable (Extended Data Fig. 1 and Supplementary Fig."
